0\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0430? (\"Who stood behind Stalin's back?\") \u2014 Moscow: Neva, Olma Media Group, 2002. \u2014 638 \u0441. {{ISBN|978-5-7654-1771-3}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Plamper |first=Jan |title=The Stalin Cult: A Study in the Alchemy of Power |location=New Haven |year=2012}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Radzinsky |first=Edvard |year=1997 |title=Stalin: The First In-Depth Biography Based on Explosive New Documents from Russia's Secret Archive |location=New York}}\n\n: {{cite book |first=Donald |last=Rayfield |year=2005 |title=Stalin and His Hangmen: The Tyrant and Those Who Killed For Him |location=New York |publisher=Penguin |isbn=978-0-14-191419-0}}\n\n:Reynolds, David, and Vladimir Pechatnov, eds. '' The Kremlin Letters: Stalin's Wartime Correspondence with Churchill and Roosevelt'' (2019)\n\n: {{cite journal |last=Rieber |first=A. J. |year=2001 |title=Stalin, Man of the Borderlands |journal=American Historical Review |volume=106 |issue=4 |pages=1651\u20131691|doi=10.2307/2692742 |jstor=2692742 }}\n\n: Roberts, Geoffrey.  \"Stalin at the Tehran, Yalta, and Potsdam conferences.\" ''Journal of Cold War Studies'' 9.4 (2007): 6\u201340.\n\n:{{cite book |last= Thurston|first=Robert W.|date=1998 |title=Life and Terror in Stalin's Russia, 1934\u20131941|url= |location= |publisher=[[Yale University Press]] |isbn=978-0-300-07442-0|author-link=Robert W. Thurston}}\n\n: {{cite book |last1=Torchinov |first1=V.A. |last2=Leontyuk |first2=A.M. |title=Around Stalin. An historical and biographical reference |year=2000 |publisher=Philological Faculty Saint-Petersburg University  |location=St Petersburg |isbn=978-5-846-50005-1|ref=harv}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Tucker |first=Robert C. |year=1973 |title=Stalin as Revolutionary: 1879\u20131929: A Study in History and Personality|publisher=New York, Norton |url=https://archive.org/details/stalinasrevoluti00tuck |url-access=registration }}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Tucker |first=Robert C. |year=1990 |title=Stalin in Power: The Revolution from Above, 1928\u20131941 |url=https://archive.org/details/stalininpowerrev00tuck |url-access=registration |location=New York}}\n\n: {{cite book |last=Ulam |first=Adam B. |year=1973 |title=Stalin: The Man and His Era |publisher=New York, Viking Press |url=https://archive.org/details/stalinmanhisera00ulam |url-access=registration |location=New York}}\n\n:Uldricks,  Teddy J. \"War, Politics and Memory: Russian Historians Reevaluate the Origins of World War II,\" ''History and Memory'' 21#2 (2009), pp. 60\u201382 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.2979/his.2009.21.2.60 online], historiography\n\n: {{cite book |last=van Ree |first=Erik |year=2002 |title= The Political Thought of Joseph Stalin: A Study in Twentieth-Century Revolutionary Patriotism |location=London and New York}}\n\n: Weinberg, Gerhard L.  (1994) ''A World at Arms: A Global History of World War II'' (1994) [https://archive.org/details/worldatarmsgloba00wein online free]\n\n: {{cite journal|author=Wheatcroft, Stephen G. |title=Victims of Stalinism and the Soviet Secret Police: The Comparability and Reliability of the Archival Data. Not the Last Word|journal= [[Europe-Asia Studies]]|volume= 51|issue= 2 |year=1999|url=http://sovietinfo.tripod.com/WCR-Secret_Police.pdf|pages=340\u2013342|doi=10.1080/09668139999056 }}\n\n: {{cite journal|jstor=20030017|title=Twenty Years of Russo-German Relations: 1919-1939|journal=Foreign Affairs|volume=25|issue=1|pages=23\u201343|last1=Wheeler-Bennett|first1=John W.|year=1946|doi=10.2307/20030017}}\n\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links\n| wikt = Stalin\n| commons = \u0418\u043e\u0441\u0438\u0444 \u0412\u0438\u0441\u0441\u0430\u0440\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u043d\n |b = no\n |n = no\n |q =Joseph Stalin\n |s =Author:Joseph Stalin\n |v = no\n | species = no\n |d = Q855\n}}\n{{Refbegin}}\n* {{Britannica|562617}}\n* [http://www.marx2mao.com/Stalin/Index.html Stalin Library (with all 13 volumes of Stalin's ''w